{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "DryDepositionParticle",
        "description": "Composite particle dry-deposition model from Seinfeld & Pandis (2006), Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics, 2nd ed., Chapter 19 (Dry Deposition). Given the surface-layer friction velocity and an aerosol particle's properties it computes the particle dry deposition velocity v_d (Eq. 19.7) and the resulting downward deposition flux F (Eq. 19.1). Eq. 19.7, v_d = 1/(r_a + r_b + r_a*r_b*v_s) + v_s, combines the resistance-network pathway -- turbulent transport through the aerodynamic resistance r_a and the quasi-laminar boundary-layer resistance r_b, with the r_a*r_b*v_s cross term capturing gravitational settling acting inside the resistance network -- with a direct gravitational-settling term v_s; the flux F = -v_d*C (Eq. 19.1) is negative for downward transport. The competition between Brownian diffusion (efficient for sub-0.1 um particles) and inertial impaction (efficient for super-um particles) leaves a deposition-velocity minimum at accumulation-mode sizes. Migrated from AtmosphericDeposition.jl@e4468c79 src/seinfeld_pandis_ch19.jl:479 (the DryDepositionParticle @component), which composes three MTK subsystems via System(eqs, t; systems=[aero, settling, qlam]). Represented here as a subsystem-composed ESS model (spec \u00a74.7): the aero subsystem inlines the already-migrated AerodynamicResistance component (aerodynamic_resistance.esm, esm-x8pg), settling inlines ParticleSettling (particle_settling.esm, esm-egwt) and qlam inlines QuasiLaminarResistanceParticle (quasi_laminar_particle.esm, esm-brbr), wired by six top-level coupling equations. Purely algebraic (no D() time-derivative anywhere): u_star and C are input parameters; v_d and F are algebraic state outputs.",
        "tags": [
            "atmospheric_deposition",
            "seinfeld-pandis",
            "sp-ch19",
            "dry-deposition",
            "particle-deposition",
            "deposition-velocity",
            "composed",
            "observed-only"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-17T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "AtmosphericDeposition.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (esm-30bn)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Seinfeld, J. H., & Pandis, S. N. (2006). Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics: From Air Pollution to Climate Change, 2nd ed., Chapter 19: Dry Deposition. John Wiley & Sons, Inc. Eq. 19.7 (particle dry deposition velocity), Eq. 19.1 (deposition flux). ISBN 978-0-471-72018-8."
            },
            {
                "citation": "Zhang, L., Gong, S., Padro, J., & Barrie, L. (2001). A size-segregated particle dry deposition scheme for an atmospheric aerosol module. Atmospheric Environment, 35(3), 549-560. https://doi.org/10.1016/S1352-2310(00)00326-5. Source of the size-resolved particle quasi-laminar resistance adopted as Eq. 19.27 by Seinfeld & Pandis (2006)."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "DryDepositionParticle": {
            "reference": {
                "citation": "Seinfeld, J. H., & Pandis, S. N. (2006). Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics: From Air Pollution to Climate Change, 2nd ed., Ch. 19, Eq. 19.7 (particle dry deposition velocity) and Eq. 19.1 (deposition flux). John Wiley & Sons, Inc.",
                "notes": "source_ref: AtmosphericDeposition.jl@e4468c79c8dd4aae88646cd16d6bcf290874742c:src/seinfeld_pandis_ch19.jl:479\nUpstream `DryDepositionParticle` is an MTK `@component` that composes three subsystems -- `@named aero = AerodynamicResistance()`, `@named settling = ParticleSettling()` and `@named qlam = QuasiLaminarResistanceParticle()` -- via `System(eqs, t; systems=[aero, settling, qlam])`, with its own input `@variables` u_star, C, the output `@variables` v_d, F, and six coupling equations. It implements Seinfeld & Pandis (2006) Ch. 19 Eq. 19.7 (particle dry deposition velocity) and Eq. 19.1 (deposition flux).\n\nSubsystem-composed migration (ESS spec \u00a74.7). The three subsystems inline the `variables` + `equations` of the already-migrated standalone components: `aero` <- aerodynamic_resistance.esm (esm-x8pg), `settling` <- particle_settling.esm (esm-egwt), `qlam` <- quasi_laminar_particle.esm (esm-brbr) -- all siblings in components/atmospheric_deposition/sp_ch19/. The six upstream coupling equations are carried as the model's top-level `equations`; subsystem variables are referenced by full dotted path from the model name (spec \u00a74.6, e.g. DryDepositionParticle.aero.r_a), bare names resolve to the top-level system. The closest precedent is sp_ch1/water_vapor_thermo.esm (esm-tfh2), a composed model with top-level coupling equations plus inlined subsystems; see also gaschem/combined/tropospheric_chemistry.esm and the coupling.couple migration pattern.\n\nVariable typing. Top-level: u_star and C are upstream input `@variables` (input=true) with no defining equation -- they migrate as input `parameter`s; v_d and F are equation-defined outputs and migrate as `state`. Re-typing: in the standalone .esm files a component's connected inputs are typed `parameter` (no governing equation within the component). In the composed model the parent coupling equations govern four such inputs -- aero.u_star (by aero.u_star ~ u_star), qlam.u_star (by qlam.u_star ~ u_star), qlam.v_s (by qlam.v_s ~ settling.v_s) and qlam.D_diff (by qlam.D_diff ~ settling.D_diff) -- so those four are re-typed `parameter` -> `state` here, because a `parameter` cannot be an equation left-hand side. Every other subsystem variable keeps its standalone type and default. The settling subsystem has no re-typed variables: its outputs v_s and D_diff are defined by settling's own equations (they appear only on coupling right-hand sides) and stay `state`.\n\nPurely algebraic. There is no `D()` time-derivative anywhere in the upstream module -- DryDepositionParticle and all three subsystems are algebraic. `system_kind` is left unset (the `ode` schema default; zero differential states), the convention of every sp_ch19 sibling. The composed model is migrated with the coupling.couple `type: state` + `equations` form (the pure-algebraic `type: observed` + empty-`equations` form is not applicable: a composed model must carry its coupling relations as `equations`, and a coupling left-hand side such as qlam.u_star must be a `state`, not an `observed` quantity). The flattened system is 16 algebraic equations in 16 states, fully explicit and triangular along the chain u_star -> aero.r_a, particle properties -> settling.v_s/D_diff -> qlam.* -> v_d -> F.\n\nIndependent D_p and g. Upstream, the settling and qlam subsystems each declare their own D_p (particle diameter) and g (gravitational acceleration); there is no coupling equation between settling.D_p and qlam.D_p, so the migration keeps them as independent parameters, faithful to the upstream `systems=[...]` structure. Every inline test sets settling.D_p and qlam.D_p to the same physical value. The settling subsystem's rho_p, D_p, mu, T and C_c carry no `default`, faithful to the standalone particle_settling.esm where they are required inputs; every test supplies them via parameter_overrides. g, k_B, pi_val and kappa keep their upstream constant defaults.\n\nNo `examples` block. `tools/render_example_plots.py` resolves algebraic models on the top-level model only and does not descend into `subsystems`, so plots of the combined-diagnostic outputs cannot be rendered -- matching the composed siblings water_vapor_thermo.esm, radiation_fundamentals.esm and tropospheric_chemistry.esm. Verification is via the inline-test gate (run_esm_inline_tests.py -> earthsci_toolkit.simulation.simulate), which flattens subsystems. Inline-test references use fully-qualified names (Model.sub.var, Model.var): the composed model has name-colliding variables across scopes (u_star top-level + aero.u_star + qlam.u_star; v_s in settling + qlam; D_diff in settling + qlam; D_p and g in settling + qlam), so the bare-suffix fallback in the runner's variable resolver would be ambiguous -- full names are unambiguous.\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-6): an observed-only triangular algebraic system, no ODE integration. Each output is a closed-form composition of +, -, *, /, ^, log, exp and sqrt evaluated once per test point; float64 round-off is ~1e-16 per operation, so rel=1e-6 leaves wide headroom across the tested ranges (r_a ~ 1e1, r_b ~ 1e1 to 4e3, v_d ~ 1e-4 to 2e-2, F ~ -1e-13 to -2e-11). Every asserted value is comfortably nonzero, so no `abs` floor is needed. Test values are the float64 evaluation of the migrated equations; the aero.r_a, settling.v_s and settling.D_diff assertions reproduce the exact values pinned by the standalone aerodynamic_resistance.esm and particle_settling.esm migrations.\n\nTests. Seven inline tests sweep the physically meaningful regimes: default_canonical pins the full coupling chain for a 1 um grassland particle and re-checks v_d/F at t=1 (time-invariance); coarse_particle (10 um) and ultrafine_particle (10 nm) exercise the settling-dominated and diffusion-dominated limbs of Eq. 19.7; strong_turbulence and weak_turbulence sweep the friction-velocity dependence of r_a and r_b; deciduous_forest exercises the land-use dependence threaded through the aero and qlam subsystems; dense_dust_particle doubles the particle density. Upstream `seinfeld_pandis_ch19_test.jl` provides only a structural test for the assembled DryDepositionParticle component, so the numerical assertions here are the float64 evaluation of the migrated equations."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1e-06
            },
            "variables": {
                "u_star": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "default": 0.4,
                    "description": "Friction velocity characterizing surface-layer turbulence -- input to the composite, fed to the aero and qlam subsystems by the coupling equations aero.u_star ~ u_star and qlam.u_star ~ u_star. Upstream an input @variable; an input parameter in the composed model. Default 0.4 m/s (canonical neutral surface layer)."
                },
                "C": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/m^3",
                    "default": 1e-09,
                    "description": "Particle (aerosol) mass concentration at the reference height -- input to the composite, used by the flux equation F = -v_d*C. Upstream an input @variable; an input parameter in the composed model. Default 1e-9 kg/m^3 (~1 ug/m^3)."
                },
                "v_d": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "description": "Particle dry deposition velocity (Eq. 19.7) -- composite output combining the aerodynamic and quasi-laminar resistances with the gravitational settling velocity."
                },
                "F": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "kg/(m^2*s)",
                    "description": "Particle dry deposition flux (Eq. 19.1), F = -v_d*C; negative for downward (toward-surface) transport."
                }
            },
            "subsystems": {
                "aero": {
                    "variables": {
                        "kappa": {
                            "type": "parameter",
                            "units": "1",
                            "default": 0.4,
                            "description": "Von Karman constant (dimensionless), upstream @constant KAPPA. Sets the slope of the neutral-stability logarithmic wind profile."
                        },
                        "z": {
                            "type": "parameter",
                            "units": "m",
                            "default": 10.0,
                            "description": "Reference height above the surface at which the aerodynamic resistance is evaluated."
                        },
                        "z_0": {
                            "type": "parameter",
                            "units": "m",
                            "default": 0.1,
                            "description": "Surface roughness length."
                        },
                        "u_star": {
                            "type": "state",
                            "units": "m/s",
                            "default": 0.4,
                            "description": "Friction velocity -- coupled input, driven by the parent coupling equation DryDepositionParticle.aero.u_star ~ u_star (re-typed parameter -> state for the composed model)."
                        },
                        "r_a": {
                            "type": "state",
                            "units": "s/m",
                            "description": "Aerodynamic resistance to dry deposition through the surface layer under neutral atmospheric stability (Eq. 19.14)."
                        }
                    },
                    "equations": [
                        {
                            "_comment": "Eq. 19.14 -- neutral-stability aerodynamic resistance: r_a = (1/(kappa*u_star)) * ln(z/z_0).",
                            "lhs": "r_a",
                            "rhs": {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [
                                            1,
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "kappa",
                                                    "u_star"
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "log",
                                        "args": [
                                            {
                                                "op": "/",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "z",
                                                    "z_0"
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                "settling": {
                    "variables": {
                        "rho_p": {
                            "type": "parameter",
                            "units": "kg/m^3",
                            "description": "Particle density (external input; carries no default, faithful to the standalone particle_settling.esm)."
                        },
                        "D_p": {
                            "type": "parameter",
                            "units": "m",
                            "description": "Particle diameter (external input; carries no default, faithful to the standalone particle_settling.esm)."
                        },
                        "mu": {
                            "type": "parameter",
                            "units": "Pa*s",
                            "description": "Dynamic viscosity of air (external input; carries no default, faithful to the standalone particle_settling.esm)."
                        },
                        "T": {
                            "type": "parameter",
                            "units": "K",
                            "description": "Temperature (external input; carries no default, faithful to the standalone particle_settling.esm)."
                        },
                        "C_c": {
                            "type": "parameter",
                            "units": "1",
                            "description": "Cunningham slip correction factor (dimensionless; external input, carries no default, faithful to the standalone particle_settling.esm)."
                        },
                        "g": {
                            "type": "parameter",
                            "units": "m/s^2",
                            "default": 9.81,
                            "description": "Gravitational acceleration (upstream @constant G_ACCEL)."
                        },
                        "k_B": {
                            "type": "parameter",
                            "units": "J/K",
                            "default": 1.38e-23,
                            "description": "Boltzmann constant (upstream @constant K_BOLTZ)."
                        },
                        "pi_val": {
                            "type": "parameter",
                            "units": "1",
                            "default": 3.141592653589793,
                            "description": "Mathematical constant pi (dimensionless; upstream @constant pi_val = Float64(pi))."
                        },
                        "v_s": {
                            "type": "state",
                            "units": "m/s",
                            "description": "Particle gravitational (Stokes) settling velocity (Eq. 19.18)."
                        },
                        "D_diff": {
                            "type": "state",
                            "units": "m^2/s",
                            "description": "Brownian (Stokes-Einstein) diffusivity of the particle (Eq. 19.20)."
                        }
                    },
                    "equations": [
                        {
                            "_comment": "Eq. 19.18 -- Stokes settling velocity with Cunningham slip correction: v_s = rho_p*D_p^2*g*C_c/(18*mu).",
                            "lhs": "v_s",
                            "rhs": {
                                "op": "/",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            "rho_p",
                                            {
                                                "op": "^",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "D_p",
                                                    2
                                                ]
                                            },
                                            "g",
                                            "C_c"
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            18,
                                            "mu"
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "_comment": "Eq. 19.20 -- Brownian (Stokes-Einstein) diffusivity with Cunningham slip correction: D_diff = k_B*T*C_c/(3*pi*mu*D_p).",
                            "lhs": "D_diff",
                            "rhs": {
                                "op": "/",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            "k_B",
                                            "T",
                                            "C_c"
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            3,
                                            "pi_val",
                                            "mu",
                                            "D_p"
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                "qlam": {
                    "variables": {
                        "nu": {
                            "type": "parameter",
                            "units": "m^2/s",
                            "default": 1.5e-05,
                            "description": "Kinematic viscosity of air."
                        },
                        "A": {
                            "type": "parameter",
                            "units": "m",
                            "default": 0.002,
                            "description": "Characteristic radius of surface collectors (Zhang et al. 2001, Table 19.2; default LANDUSE_GRASS)."
                        },
                        "alpha": {
                            "type": "parameter",
                            "units": "1",
                            "default": 1.2,
                            "description": "Impaction efficiency parameter of the land-use category (Zhang et al. 2001, Table 19.2; default LANDUSE_GRASS) (dimensionless)."
                        },
                        "gamma": {
                            "type": "parameter",
                            "units": "1",
                            "default": 0.54,
                            "description": "Brownian diffusion efficiency exponent of the land-use category (Zhang et al. 2001, Table 19.2; default LANDUSE_GRASS) (dimensionless)."
                        },
                        "D_p": {
                            "type": "parameter",
                            "units": "m",
                            "default": 1e-06,
                            "description": "Particle diameter. Upstream the qlam subsystem declares its own D_p, independent of settling.D_p; both are set to the same physical value in every inline test."
                        },
                        "g": {
                            "type": "parameter",
                            "units": "m/s^2",
                            "default": 9.81,
                            "description": "Gravitational acceleration (upstream @constant G_ACCEL)."
                        },
                        "u_star": {
                            "type": "state",
                            "units": "m/s",
                            "default": 0.4,
                            "description": "Friction velocity -- coupled input, driven by the parent coupling equation DryDepositionParticle.qlam.u_star ~ u_star (re-typed parameter -> state for the composed model)."
                        },
                        "v_s": {
                            "type": "state",
                            "units": "m/s",
                            "default": 3.5e-05,
                            "description": "Particle settling velocity -- coupled input, driven by the parent coupling equation DryDepositionParticle.qlam.v_s ~ DryDepositionParticle.settling.v_s (re-typed parameter -> state for the composed model)."
                        },
                        "D_diff": {
                            "type": "state",
                            "units": "m^2/s",
                            "default": 2.7e-11,
                            "description": "Brownian diffusivity of the particle -- coupled input, driven by the parent coupling equation DryDepositionParticle.qlam.D_diff ~ DryDepositionParticle.settling.D_diff (re-typed parameter -> state for the composed model)."
                        },
                        "Sc": {
                            "type": "state",
                            "units": "1",
                            "description": "Particle Schmidt number, Sc = nu/D_diff (dimensionless)."
                        },
                        "St": {
                            "type": "state",
                            "units": "1",
                            "description": "Stokes number for vegetated surfaces, St = v_s*u_star/(g*A) (Eq. 19.24) (dimensionless)."
                        },
                        "E_B": {
                            "type": "state",
                            "units": "1",
                            "description": "Brownian diffusion collection efficiency, E_B = Sc^(-gamma) (Eq. 19.21) (dimensionless)."
                        },
                        "E_IM": {
                            "type": "state",
                            "units": "1",
                            "description": "Inertial impaction collection efficiency, E_IM = (St/(alpha+St))^2 (Eq. 19.22, beta = 2) (dimensionless)."
                        },
                        "E_IN": {
                            "type": "state",
                            "units": "1",
                            "description": "Interception collection efficiency, E_IN = 0.5*(D_p/A)^2 (Eq. 19.25) (dimensionless)."
                        },
                        "R_1": {
                            "type": "state",
                            "units": "1",
                            "description": "Sticking (rebound-correction) fraction, R_1 = exp(-sqrt(St)) (Eq. 19.26) (dimensionless)."
                        },
                        "r_b": {
                            "type": "state",
                            "units": "s/m",
                            "description": "Quasi-laminar (boundary-layer) resistance for the particle, Eq. 19.27 (Zhang et al. 2001)."
                        }
                    },
                    "equations": [
                        {
                            "_comment": "Particle Schmidt number: Sc = nu/D_diff.",
                            "lhs": "Sc",
                            "rhs": {
                                "op": "/",
                                "args": [
                                    "nu",
                                    "D_diff"
                                ]
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "_comment": "Eq. 19.24 -- Stokes number for vegetated surfaces: St = v_s*u_star/(g*A).",
                            "lhs": "St",
                            "rhs": {
                                "op": "/",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            "v_s",
                                            "u_star"
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            "g",
                                            "A"
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "_comment": "Eq. 19.21 -- Brownian diffusion collection efficiency: E_B = Sc^(-gamma).",
                            "lhs": "E_B",
                            "rhs": {
                                "op": "^",
                                "args": [
                                    "Sc",
                                    {
                                        "op": "-",
                                        "args": [
                                            "gamma"
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "_comment": "Eq. 19.22 -- inertial impaction collection efficiency, beta = 2: E_IM = (St/(alpha+St))^2.",
                            "lhs": "E_IM",
                            "rhs": {
                                "op": "^",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [
                                            "St",
                                            {
                                                "op": "+",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "alpha",
                                                    "St"
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    2
                                ]
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "_comment": "Eq. 19.25 -- interception collection efficiency: E_IN = 0.5*(D_p/A)^2.",
                            "lhs": "E_IN",
                            "rhs": {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    0.5,
                                    {
                                        "op": "^",
                                        "args": [
                                            {
                                                "op": "/",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "D_p",
                                                    "A"
                                                ]
                                            },
                                            2
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "_comment": "Eq. 19.26 -- sticking fraction / rebound correction: R_1 = exp(-sqrt(St)).",
                            "lhs": "R_1",
                            "rhs": {
                                "op": "exp",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "-",
                                        "args": [
                                            {
                                                "op": "sqrt",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "St"
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "_comment": "Eq. 19.27 -- quasi-laminar resistance for particles, Zhang et al. (2001): r_b = 1/(3*u_star*(E_B+E_IM+E_IN)*R_1).",
                            "lhs": "r_b",
                            "rhs": {
                                "op": "/",
                                "args": [
                                    1,
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            3,
                                            "u_star",
                                            {
                                                "op": "+",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "E_B",
                                                    "E_IM",
                                                    "E_IN"
                                                ]
                                            },
                                            "R_1"
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "_comment": "Couple the friction velocity into the aerodynamic-resistance subsystem (upstream: aero.u_star ~ u_star).",
                    "lhs": "DryDepositionParticle.aero.u_star",
                    "rhs": "u_star"
                },
                {
                    "_comment": "Couple the friction velocity into the quasi-laminar-resistance subsystem (upstream: qlam.u_star ~ u_star).",
                    "lhs": "DryDepositionParticle.qlam.u_star",
                    "rhs": "u_star"
                },
                {
                    "_comment": "Feed the settling velocity from the settling subsystem into the quasi-laminar subsystem (upstream: qlam.v_s ~ settling.v_s).",
                    "lhs": "DryDepositionParticle.qlam.v_s",
                    "rhs": "DryDepositionParticle.settling.v_s"
                },
                {
                    "_comment": "Feed the Brownian diffusivity from the settling subsystem into the quasi-laminar subsystem (upstream: qlam.D_diff ~ settling.D_diff).",
                    "lhs": "DryDepositionParticle.qlam.D_diff",
                    "rhs": "DryDepositionParticle.settling.D_diff"
                },
                {
                    "_comment": "Eq. 19.7 -- particle dry deposition velocity: v_d = 1/(r_a + r_b + r_a*r_b*v_s) + v_s. The 1/(...) term is the resistance-network pathway (aerodynamic + quasi-laminar, with the r_a*r_b*v_s cross term for settling within the network); the trailing + v_s is direct gravitational settling.",
                    "lhs": "v_d",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "/",
                                "args": [
                                    1,
                                    {
                                        "op": "+",
                                        "args": [
                                            "DryDepositionParticle.aero.r_a",
                                            "DryDepositionParticle.qlam.r_b",
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "DryDepositionParticle.aero.r_a",
                                                    "DryDepositionParticle.qlam.r_b",
                                                    "DryDepositionParticle.settling.v_s"
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            "DryDepositionParticle.settling.v_s"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "_comment": "Eq. 19.1 -- dry deposition flux: F = -v_d*C. The negative sign marks downward (toward the surface) transport.",
                    "lhs": "F",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "-",
                                "args": [
                                    "v_d"
                                ]
                            },
                            "C"
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "default_canonical",
                    "description": "Canonical case: a 1 um unit-density (rho_p = 1000 kg/m^3) accumulation-mode particle depositing over grassland (aero z = 10 m, z_0 = 0.1 m; qlam Zhang et al. 2001 Table 19.2 grassland A = 2 mm, alpha = 1.2, gamma = 0.54) in a neutral surface layer with friction velocity u_star = 0.4 m/s. Verifies the full coupling chain: u_star feeds the aero and qlam subsystems, the settling subsystem produces v_s and D_diff from the particle properties, those are wired into qlam (qlam.v_s = settling.v_s, qlam.D_diff = settling.D_diff), and Eq. 19.7 combines aero.r_a, qlam.r_b and settling.v_s into v_d (~0.94 mm/s -- the accumulation-mode deposition-velocity minimum). The flux F = -v_d*C is the downward (negative) deposition flux for C = 1e-9 kg/m^3 (~1 ug/m^3 aerosol mass). The system is algebraic, so v_d and F are also re-checked at t = 1 to confirm time-invariance.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "DryDepositionParticle.u_star": 0.4,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.C": 1e-09,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.aero.z": 10.0,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.aero.z_0": 0.1,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.settling.rho_p": 1000.0,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.settling.D_p": 1e-06,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.settling.mu": 1.85e-05,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.settling.T": 298.0,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.settling.C_c": 1.16,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.qlam.nu": 1.5e-05,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.qlam.A": 0.002,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.qlam.alpha": 1.2,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.qlam.gamma": 0.54,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.qlam.D_p": 1e-06
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "DryDepositionParticle.aero.r_a",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 28.78231366242557
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "DryDepositionParticle.settling.v_s",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 3.417297297297298e-05
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "DryDepositionParticle.settling.D_diff",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 2.7359646632305877e-11
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "DryDepositionParticle.qlam.Sc",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 548252.6949850374
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "DryDepositionParticle.qlam.St",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.0006966966966966968
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "DryDepositionParticle.qlam.E_B",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.0007960683935895912
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "DryDepositionParticle.qlam.r_b",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 1074.1867306540298
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "DryDepositionParticle.v_d",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.0009399490791867023
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "DryDepositionParticle.F",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": -9.399490791867023e-13
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "DryDepositionParticle.v_d",
                            "time": 1.0,
                            "expected": 0.0009399490791867023
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "DryDepositionParticle.F",
                            "time": 1.0,
                            "expected": -9.399490791867023e-13
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "coarse_particle",
                    "description": "A 10 um coarse particle (D_p = 1e-5 m in both the settling and qlam subsystems, Cunningham slip correction C_c = 1.0 in the continuum limit), grassland and u_star = 0.4 m/s otherwise as default_canonical. The large diameter raises the Stokes settling velocity v_s ~ 2.9 mm/s by the Eq. 19.18 D_p^2 dependence, so the direct gravitational-settling term of Eq. 19.7 now dominates the deposition velocity: v_d ~ 5.0 mm/s, well above the 1 um case. v_d is re-checked at t = 1 for time-invariance.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "DryDepositionParticle.u_star": 0.4,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.C": 1e-09,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.aero.z": 10.0,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.aero.z_0": 0.1,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.settling.rho_p": 1000.0,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.settling.D_p": 1e-05,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.settling.mu": 1.85e-05,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.settling.T": 298.0,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.settling.C_c": 1.0,
