                {
                    "id": "ultrafine_particle",
                    "description": "A 10 nm ultrafine particle (D_p = 1e-8 m, large Cunningham slip correction C_c = 22.0), grassland and u_star = 0.4 m/s otherwise as default_canonical. The tiny diameter gives a large Brownian diffusivity D_diff ~ 5.2e-8 m^2/s (Eq. 19.20, D_diff proportional to 1/D_p), a small particle Schmidt number Sc ~ 289, and a strong Brownian-diffusion collection efficiency E_B -- so the Zhang et al. quasi-laminar resistance r_b collapses to ~18 s/m. With r_b small the resistance-network term of Eq. 19.7 dominates and v_d ~ 21 mm/s, the diffusion-controlled limb of the particle dry-deposition curve.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "DryDepositionParticle.u_star": 0.4,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.C": 1e-09,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.aero.z": 10.0,
