                            "expected": -2.1470320955214066e-11
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "strong_turbulence",
                    "description": "The default 1 um grassland particle in a strongly turbulent surface layer, u_star = 1.0 m/s (2.5x the default). The higher friction velocity lowers both the aerodynamic resistance r_a (Eq. 19.14, r_a proportional to 1/u_star) and the quasi-laminar resistance r_b (Eq. 19.27, the explicit 1/(3*u_star) factor), so the resistance-network pathway of Eq. 19.7 transports the particle to the surface faster and v_d ~ 2.3 mm/s rises above the default case. The settling velocity v_s is unchanged (u_star does not enter Eq. 19.18).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "DryDepositionParticle.u_star": 1.0,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.C": 1e-09,
                        "DryDepositionParticle.aero.z": 10.0,
