                {
                    "id": "deciduous_forest",
                    "description": "The default 1 um particle depositing over a deciduous forest: a rough canopy (aero z_0 = 1.0 m) with the Zhang et al. 2001 Table 19.2 deciduous-forest land-use category in qlam (A = 5 mm, alpha = 0.6, gamma = 0.56). The larger roughness length lowers the aerodynamic resistance r_a relative to grassland, while the larger collector radius A raises the quasi-laminar resistance r_b (lower Stokes number and interception efficiency); the two effects partly cancel, leaving v_d ~ 0.75 mm/s near the grassland default. Exercises the land-use dependence threaded through both the aero and qlam subsystems.",
